The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Makramah posts upset victory 

 OUR TURF CORRESPONDENT

 Makramah scored an upset victory 

 in the Adler Trophy at the Mumbai races on Saturday. Apprentice 

 Riyaz Shaikh partnered the Robert DMellow-trained 

 ward to victory. 

 The afternoon also witnessed a popular double by the ex-city trainer, Bharath Singh. His strongly-supported ward Nimble Feet claimed the 1,400m Littleover Trophy. The trainers Lone Trojan followed it up with an easy win in the Bhishma Plate.

